Hi there,

Thanks for what looks like a great engine!

I was hoping to get the most basic startup/shutdown code possible. Although I have successfully built the library from source, I'm using the latest Windows static lib release in a new Visual Studio Project. So far, I've gotten nothing but linking errors (LNK2018 Unresolved external). The code I'm using is this:

``` C++
#include "stdafx.h"
#include "Engine.h"
#include "Ptr.h"

int _tmain(int argc, _TCHAR* argv[])
{
    Urho3D::SharedPtr<Urho3D::Engine> engine;
    Urho3D::Context* context;
    engine = new Urho3D::Engine(context);
    engine->Exit();
    return -1;
}
```

Is this correct? If I simply link/include the static lib and add the include directly to my new VS2012 project, should I be able to run the engine? Or am I missing something.

I know platform specific building questions are a bit frustrating, but any help would be most appreciated.
